The paper deals with the problem of multi-object tracking in a complex scene captured by a single camera, which is a common problem in computer vision. The proposed method involves joint learning of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and temporally constrained metrics, which are commonly used in computer vision and machine learning. The paper also discusses the use of a novel loss function incorporating temporally constrained multi-task learning mechanism, which is a common technique in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Other likely sub-categories include cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.RO (Robotics).
